  "course_description": "Part of Emory's Voluntary Core Curriculum. Certain great books have been influential across the centuries, and continue to influence the way we think, act, and understand ourselves today. Major themes of the course are the history of religion, politics, economics, biology, and psychology.",
  "course_notes": "The course is part of Emory College's Voluntary Core Curriculum Program. This course offers students the chance to read some of the most important books ever written, whose lessons have remained relevant to multiple generations through the centuries. Included are works by Julius Caesar, Machiavelli, Adam Smith, Thomas Malthus, John Stuart Mill, Karl Marx, Charles Darwin, Sigmund Freud, and John Maynard Keynes. Close reading and engaged discussion, short writing assignments, two midterms and a final exam.",
